## Should you integrate call tracking with attribution?

You have two architectural choices:

<div class="my-6 not-prose grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
  <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-slate-200">
    <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-800 mb-4">Integrated (Ruler Analytics)</h4>
    <div class="mb-4">
      <p class="text-xs text-emerald-600 font-medium uppercase mb-2">Pros</p>
      <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-slate-700">
        <li>Single tool, single vendor</li>
        <li>Pre-integrated data</li>
        <li>Simpler setup</li>
        <li>Unified reporting</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div>
      <p class="text-xs text-rose-600 font-medium uppercase mb-2">Cons</p>
      <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-slate-700">
        <li>May not be the best at either</li>
        <li>Vendor lock-in</li>
        <li>Less flexibility</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="bg-indigo-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-indigo-200">
    <h4 class="font-semibold text-indigo-800 mb-4">Separate (e.g. CallRail + attribution tool)</h4>
    <div class="mb-4">
      <p class="text-xs text-emerald-600 font-medium uppercase mb-2">Pros</p>
      <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-indigo-900">
        <li>Best at each function</li>
        <li>Flexibility to swap components</li>
        <li>Deeper capabilities per tool</li>
        <li>Can add model flexibility</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div>
      <p class="text-xs text-rose-600 font-medium uppercase mb-2">Cons</p>
      <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-indigo-900">
        <li>Integration required</li>
        <li>Multiple vendors</li>
        <li>More complex setup</li>
        <li>Higher total cost potentially</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

For most businesses, the question is: **How important is call tracking vs. attribution accuracy?**

- Calls are primary → CallRail/Invoca + lighter attribution
- Attribution accuracy is primary → Dedicated attribution tool + call tracking integration

